From: Dustin Kirkland <dustin.kirkland@chainguard.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix gettid() for glibc < 2.30 build environments

gettid() became a glibc wrapper only in glibc 2.30. PHP's config.h,
built on a newer host, may define HAVE_GETTID=1 even when the actual
build environment uses an older glibc (e.g. eco-2-28 using glibc 2.28).
This causes the existing syscall fallback in timerlib_posix.c to be
skipped, resulting in "implicit declaration of function 'gettid'" errors.

Insert a glibc version check that clears HAVE_GETTID on glibc < 2.30,
ensuring the syscall(SYS_gettid) fallback is always active on older builds.

--- a/timerlib/timerlib_posix.c
+++ b/timerlib/timerlib_posix.c
@@ -58,6 +58,12 @@
 }
 #endif

+/* gettid() was added as a glibc wrapper in glibc 2.30. PHP's config.h,
+ * built on a newer host, may define HAVE_GETTID=1. Clear it for glibc < 2.30
+ * so the syscall(SYS_gettid) fallback below is always active on older builds. */
+#if defined(__GLIBC__) && (__GLIBC__ == 2) && (__GLIBC_MINOR__ < 30)
+#undef HAVE_GETTID
+#endif
 #ifndef HAVE_GETTID
 #include <sys/syscall.h>
 #define gettid() ((pid_t)syscall(SYS_gettid))
